  <heading>LD1B (scalar plus vector)</heading>
  <desc>
    <brief>Gather load unsigned bytes to vector (vector index)</brief>
    <description>
      <para>Gather load of unsigned bytes to active elements of a vector register from memory addresses generated by a 64-bit scalar base plus vector index. The index values are optionally sign or zero-extended from 32 to 64 bits. Inactive elements will not read Device memory or signal faults, and are set to zero in the destination vector.</para>
    </description>
    <status>Green</status>
    <predicated>True</predicated>
  </desc>
  <alias_list howmany="0"></alias_list>
